outcome_space.description: US Initial Jobless Claims (Thousands, Seasonally Adjusted)

base_case.condition: What will the US Initial Jobless Claims be for the week ending {observation.reference_date}?
base_case.fsp_resolution: FSP equals the seasonally adjusted number of initial jobless claims (in thousands) for the week ending {observation.reference_date}, as reported by the U.S. Department of Labor, Employment and Training Administration, and released on {observation.release_date}. Claims values are scaled by 0.001 (e.g., 241,000 claims settles as 241). This data is available via the FRED API (Series ID: ICSA).

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Department of Labor announces that it cannot produce the Initial Jobless Claims number for the week ending {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances (such as government shutdown) but provides an alternative estimate or proxy value.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = the alternative estimate or proxy value provided by the U.S. Department of Labor, scaled by 0.001.

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Department of Labor announces that it cannot produce the Initial Jobless Claims number for the week ending {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances and will not publish one for this period.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = {oracle_fallback.fallback_fsp}, the Initial Jobless Claims value from preceding week, {observation.reference_date} - 7days.

outcome_space.source_name: U.S. Department of Labor, Employment and Training Administration

oracle_config.description: Prototype1 oracle configuration for Initial Jobless Claims data retrieval from FRED API
